sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1866005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The assimilatory Nitrite Reductase gene under the control of a strong Promoter Anderson J23104 with a Ribosome Binding Site was cloned onto the pSB1A3 plasmid backbone. This gene catalyses the conversion of Nitrite (NO2 -) to Ammonium (NH4 +).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Oehler
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It was isolated from Escherichia coli K12 strain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K880005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Strong promoter, strong RBS combination for high expression levels of proteins
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
-J23100+B0034 -Strong promoter, strong RBS combination for high expression levels of proteins
Consensus constitutive promoter and RBS sequence-produces strongest possible expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Atkinson, Mike Ferguson, and Ben Parker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is a combination of strong promoter (J23100) and RBS (B0034).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K136006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: flgA promoter followed by its natural RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter of flgA gene from E. coli flagella
flgA is a class 2 gene that is part of the construction of the flagella ( Ordering Genes in a Flagella Pathway by Analysis of Expression Kinetics from Living Bacteria - S. Kalir, J. McClure, K. Pabbaraju, C. Southward, M. Ronen, S. Leibler, M. G. Surette, U. Alon ).
Its promoter is consitutively repressed.
It is activated by FlhD4C2 and maybe by FliA with different strength ( Using a Quantitative Blueprint to Reprogram the Dynamics of the Flagella Gene Network - Shiraz Kalir and Uri Alon ).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kok-Phen YAN
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part comes from the genome of E.coli K12 strain MG1655.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
